  - LangGraph
  - security
  - local LLM
  - Ollama
  - multi-agent
  - tool crystallization
  - prompt injection
  - Apple Silicon

references:
  - type: software
    title: "OpenClaw (née Clawdbot / Moltbot)"
    authors:
      - family-names: Steinberger
        given-names: Peter
    url: "https://github.com/openClaw"
    notes: >
      Primary inspiration for LegionForge. Proved the demand for self-hosted
      agent systems and the architectural patterns that work. Also proved the
      cost of shipping security as an afterthought — 512 post-release
      vulnerabilities and active data exfiltration in third-party skills were
      the direct motivation for LegionForge's security-first design.

  - type: software
    title: "LangGraph"
    authors:
      - name: "LangChain, Inc."
    url: "https://github.com/langchain-ai/langgraph"
    license: MIT

  - type: article
    title: "Learning to Use Tools by Making Them (LATM)"
    authors:
      - family-names: Cai
        given-names: Tianle
    year: 2024
    url: "https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.17126"
    notes: "ICLR 2024. Closest published antecedent to LegionForge-Anneal's tool crystallization pipeline."

  - type: article
    title: "Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models"
    authors:
      - family-names: Wang
        given-names: Guanzhi
    year: 2023
    url: "https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.16291"
    notes: "NVIDIA. Demonstrates lifelong tool accumulation — informs LegionForge-Anneal vision."

  - type: software
    title: "Anchor Engine — STAR: Semantic Temporal Associative Retrieval"
    authors:
      - family-names: Balch II
        given-names: Robert S.
    doi: "10.5281/zenodo.18841399"
    url: "https://github.com/RSBalchII/anchor-engine-node"
    license: "AGPL-3.0"
    notes: >
      The STAR gravity formula (similarity × e^(-λ · age)) is adapted for
      LegionForge's temporal decay path in src/database.py similarity_search().

  - type: report
    title: "The AI-Human Engineering Stack"
    authors:
      - family-names: Mill
        given-names: Hayen
      - family-names: Sanchez
        given-names: Henrique Jr.
        alias: "hjasanchez"
    year: 2026
    url: "https://github.com/hjasanchez/agentic-engineering"
    notes: >
      The Manus Insight on KV-cache stability ordering motivated the context
      assembly order in src/base_graph.py: [persona (stable) → prefs → memory → task].

  - type: article
    title: "Reflections on Trusting Trust"
    authors:
      - family-names: Thompson
        given-names: Ken
    year: 1984
    journal: "Communications of the ACM"
    notes: "The capability amplification problem in §1.9 of RESEARCH.md is a direct analogue."
